00:46:02,947 --> 00:46:04,744
I shot two squirrels.

496
00:46:07,051 --> 00:46:09,986
- What's going on?
- You scared us half to death, cocksucker.

497
00:46:10,054 --> 00:46:13,785
You don't be leaving like that,
taking a rifle without letting us know.

498
00:46:14,892 --> 00:46:16,052
Sorry.

499
00:46:17,328 --> 00:46:19,853
- Why don't you cook these?
- Fuck you.

500
00:46:21,866 --> 00:46:23,458
So, you're okay?

501
00:46:23,968 --> 00:46:25,629
Everything's okay?

502
00:46:27,104 --> 00:46:30,471
I guess, but I'm afraid
I'm not out of the woods yet.

503
00:46:33,210 --> 00:46:35,440
I'm looking for somebody that might live here...

504
00:46:35,513 --> 00:46:38,414
...an old friend of mine, his name's Jesse.

505
00:46:38,482 --> 00:46:39,972
No Jesse here.

506
00:46:40,117 --> 00:46:42,347
I think he lives with a guy named Gary.

507
00:46:42,586 --> 00:46:45,680
Gary's kind of fat, plays the drums.

508
00:46:46,790 --> 00:46:51,056
Gary Dell, he's always drumming,
driving everybody crazy.

509
00:46:51,495 --> 00:46:52,962
He's in 422.

510
00:46:53,464 --> 00:46:56,160
If he's home, you'd know it.

511
00:46:59,336 --> 00:47:02,464
- You're a pain in my ass, man.
- I know.

512
00:47:03,007 --> 00:47:06,238
- Ever since you were a kid...
- I said, yeah. Lay off.

513
00:47:07,111 --> 00:47:10,547
Thank you, fellas. Be my valentine, all right?

514
00:47:12,016 --> 00:47:14,246
What do you want? A blow job?

515
00:47:17,121 --> 00:47:18,520
I don't know.

516
00:47:22,893 --> 00:47:25,623
Y'all are my friends. You saved my ass.

517
00:47:26,797 --> 00:47:31,564
Wish there was something I could do
to really thank you.

518
00:47:32,770 --> 00:47:34,670
Are you serious about that blow job?

519
00:47:39,843 --> 00:47:41,811
Where the fuck is Jesse?

520
00:47:42,112 --> 00:47:45,206
Jesse split, man.
He's not staying here anymore.

521
00:47:45,416 --> 00:47:48,579
Look, I'm really not one of Jesse's friends.

522
00:47:49,053 --> 00:47:50,714
I should've known.

523
00:47:53,023 --> 00:47:55,583
Maybe he moved in with Bridget,
his old girlfriend.

524
00:47:55,726 --> 00:47:57,318
He said something about that.

525
00:47:57,494 --> 00:48:00,224
- Where does she live?
- Shit, I don't know.

526
00:48:01,465 --> 00:48:05,799
But she hangs out at Boardners.
Jesse hangs out there, too.

527
00:48:06,637 --> 00:48:09,128
It's on Cherokee just down from Hollywood.

528
00:48:15,546 --> 00:48:17,741
Hey, man. I'm back.

529
00:48:24,622 --> 00:48:26,112
Hey, shitheel.

530
00:48:43,540 --> 00:48:46,600
Hey, man. You okay?
Come on, open up the door.

531
00:48:48,479 --> 00:48:51,471
- What's up?
- Nothing. What are you doing?

532
00:48:52,049 --> 00:48:53,914
Sitting here thinking.

533
00:48:56,020 --> 00:48:57,817
Know what I realized?

534
00:48:58,889 --> 00:49:00,618
I was never very good at this.

535
00:49:02,359 --> 00:49:05,089
Come on, man, I got a date.
Get out of the bathroom.

536
00:49:05,429 --> 00:49:08,091
I've been meaning to talk to you
about something.

537
00:49:08,165 --> 00:49:09,291
What?

538
00:49:09,867 --> 00:49:12,131
It's about that money I got.

539
00:49:12,636 --> 00:49:14,126
Blackjack, right?

540
00:49:15,739 --> 00:49:17,104
I stole it.

541
00:49:18,308 --> 00:49:19,900
Out in LA.

542
00:49:20,611 --> 00:49:23,671
These two dudes
were trying to kill each other in a car...

543
00:49:23,747 --> 00:49:26,147
...some dope deal or something.

544
00:49:26,283 --> 00:49:29,377
I kind of stumbled on it and saw this briefcase.

545
00:49:30,721 --> 00:49:32,052
I took it.

546
00:49:32,790 --> 00:49:34,052
Are you shitting me?

547
00:49:35,092 --> 00:49:36,616
I shit you not.

548
00:49:36,994 --> 00:49:39,519
How much money are we talking about?

549
00:49:42,099 --> 00:49:43,760
$200,000.

550
00:49:44,401 --> 00:49:45,663
God damn.

551
00:49:46,704 --> 00:49:48,729
- Where is it at?
- I hid it.

552
00:49:49,073 --> 00:49:51,337
- Where did you hide it?
- I buried it.

553
00:49:53,077 --> 00:49:55,978
I just felt bad about not telling you guys.

554
00:49:57,815 --> 00:50:01,808
All right, look. We got to keep this
between me and you, for one.

555
00:50:02,986 --> 00:50:05,511
I think it might make Steve nervous.

556
00:50:07,157 --> 00:50:09,682
What are you? A fuckin' outlaw, now?

557
00:50:09,893 --> 00:50:12,054
- I guess so.
- Shit.

558
00:50:13,297 --> 00:50:16,562
They know where you are?
Can they come here and track you down?

559
00:50:17,134 --> 00:50:18,158
No.

560
00:50:20,104 --> 00:50:21,162
I don't think so.

561
00:50:55,839 --> 00:50:57,306
Hey, Bridget.

562
00:50:58,208 --> 00:51:00,335
How you doing tonight, honey?

563
00:51:02,846 --> 00:51:04,336
Where's Jesse?

564
00:51:04,748 --> 00:51:08,115
I don't know where he is. He's gone.

565
00:51:08,252 --> 00:51:09,810
I also don't know you.

566
00:51:10,254 --> 00:51:14,418
I'm sorry. I'm an old buddy of Jesse's.
He told me a lot about you.

567
00:51:14,992 --> 00:51:17,392
I thought he'd be here with you tonight.

568
00:51:17,461 --> 00:51:19,156
What can I get for you?

569
00:51:19,696 --> 00:51:22,426
Not a damn thing. Thank you, I'm fine.

570
00:51:23,100 --> 00:51:24,863
Who are you, anyway?

571
00:51:25,636 --> 00:51:28,230
Like I said, I'm a friend of Jesse's.

572
00:51:28,806 --> 00:51:31,172
I was hoping you could help us find him.

573
00:51:32,142 --> 00:51:34,076
You're not a friend of his.

574
00:51:34,144 --> 00:51:35,236
I am.

575
00:51:36,213 --> 00:51:37,908
What do you want from him?

576
00:51:39,149 --> 00:51:40,946
I just want to talk to him.

577
00:51:47,691 --> 00:51:52,424
You know something, I got a good idea.
Why don't we go look for him together?

578
00:51:56,033 --> 00:51:57,500
I don't think so.

579
00:51:58,569 --> 00:52:00,366
Come on, it'll be fun.

580
00:52:00,470 --> 00:52:05,271
Thanks for the offer, but I'll just stay here.
So just fuck off!

581
00:52:08,078 --> 00:52:09,340
Fuck off.

582
00:52:13,217 --> 00:52:16,277
Sorry, ma'am. I didn't mean to ruin your night.

583
00:52:28,932 --> 00:52:31,162
Why don't you get out of here?

584
00:53:06,303 --> 00:53:09,898
I'll ask you one more time, and then
cut your throat and find him myself.

585
00:53:09,973 --> 00:53:13,306
I'm not some fuckin' idiot.
You're not going to kill anybody here.

586
00:53:13,543 --> 00:53:16,444
You can't threaten me, you fuckin' redneck!

587
00:53:19,783 --> 00:53:21,774
Cut her a little, Calvin.

588
00:53:21,985 --> 00:53:23,384
I'd love to.

589
00:53:24,855 --> 00:53:26,117
Oh, baby.

590
00:53:32,429 --> 00:53:34,420
He left a message on my machine...

591
00:53:34,498 --> 00:53:37,729
...telling me he had to get out of town.

592
00:53:39,236 --> 00:53:43,935
He didn't tell me where. He wasn't
specific. Like San Francisco or Texas.

593
00:53:44,341 --> 00:53:48,300
- Where would he go in Texas?
- Galveston. That's where he's from.

594
00:53:48,512 --> 00:53:50,412
What's his last name? He have family?

595
00:53:50,547 --> 00:53:53,209
His granddad is from Galveston...

596
00:53:53,283 --> 00:53:56,150
...and his last name's Parish.

597
00:53:56,520 --> 00:53:59,216
I don't know anymore, really, please...

598
00:53:59,656 --> 00:54:00,987
...can I go?

599
00:54:02,092 --> 00:54:04,686
Kill her and bury her. Let's get out of here.

600
00:54:05,329 --> 00:54:07,194
- Thanks. I want to go home.
- No.

601
00:54:08,165 --> 00:54:10,565
- My God.
- It's going to be all right.

602
00:54:11,001 --> 00:54:14,459
It won't be bad, baby, don't worry.

603
00:54:35,525 --> 00:54:38,289
Do you know what time it is, you son of a bitch?

604
00:54:38,428 --> 00:54:39,895
How did you know it was me, Red?

605
00:54:41,665 --> 00:54:43,428
How's life in the Lone Star State?

606
00:54:44,334 --> 00:54:47,235
It's lonesome, partner. How about you?

607
00:54:48,605 --> 00:54:50,835
Actually, I've been a lot better.

608
00:54:50,907 --> 00:54:55,173
You never call me just to shoot the shit.
You got a problem, what is it?

609
00:54:55,312 --> 00:55:00,181
I'm looking for an old boy. I think he
might be down in your neck of the woods.

610
00:55:01,084 --> 00:55:03,882
He's got a lot of my money,
I was hoping you could find him.

611
00:55:04,388 --> 00:55:07,448
- What's his name?
- His name's Jesse.

612
00:55:07,891 --> 00:55:09,119
Jesse Parish.

613
00:55:21,605 --> 00:55:23,266
It's your granddad.

614
00:55:24,808 --> 00:55:27,606
- Granddad?
- I need to talk to you, boy.

615
00:55:29,312 --> 00:55:33,180
- Okay.
- Not on the telephone. Out here.

616
00:55:34,384 --> 00:55:36,614
- Right now?
- Right now, boy.

617
00:55:37,387 --> 00:55:38,877
You coming or ain't you?

618
00:55:38,955 --> 00:55:41,583
- Sure.
- All right, then.

619
00:55:44,528 --> 00:55:45,961
All right, then.

620
00:56:07,684 --> 00:56:09,914
- What happened?
- I did.

621
00:56:13,690 --> 00:56:15,487
I'm happening to you.

622
00:56:16,359 --> 00:56:19,055
A friend of mine says you
stole something from him.

623
00:56:19,129 --> 00:56:20,221
What friend?

624
00:56:20,297 --> 00:56:23,596
An old boy named Marshall Tanner
from Humboldt County, California.

625
00:56:23,834 --> 00:56:28,328
I don't know any Marshall Tanner.
I've never even been to Humboldt County.

626
00:56:30,373 --> 00:56:32,705
You been to LA, ain't you, baby?

627
00:56:33,143 --> 00:56:35,270
I'm looking for a briefcase.

628
00:56:36,680 --> 00:56:39,205
I can get it for you. It's no problem.

629
00:56:40,684 --> 00:56:42,777
Promise that you'll let my granddad go.

630
00:56:43,220 --> 00:56:45,745
All I care about is the money, baby.

631
00:56:49,192 --> 00:56:50,420
All right.

632
00:56:54,498 --> 00:56:55,658
Where is it at?

633
00:56:57,367 --> 00:57:00,632
I don't have it here,
but I can take you to it.

634
00:57:01,505 --> 00:57:02,767
So take me to it.

635
00:57:04,741 --> 00:57:07,107
How do I know you're not going
to kill me?

636
00:57:07,577 --> 00:57:10,102
Do I look like a killer to you, boy?

637
00:57:32,769 --> 00:57:33,997
Oh, God.

638
00:57:42,746 --> 00:57:45,340
He would've killed you for sure, boy.

639
00:57:47,050 --> 00:57:49,280
Was that his car at the fruit stand?

640
00:58:07,270 --> 00:58:08,737
Did Red call?

641
00:58:09,072 --> 00:58:11,666
He called from Galveston a while ago.

642
00:58:11,775 --> 00:58:14,539
He said he found out
where that punk's granddad lives.

643
00:58:15,111 --> 00:58:16,510
That's good.

644
00:58:17,514 --> 00:58:20,005
So Red's paying him a little visit?

645
00:58:20,383 --> 00:58:22,578
He should've already paid it.

646
00:58:23,019 --> 00:58:26,420
He said he'd call back in an hour,
that was two and half hours ago.

647
00:58:27,257 --> 00:58:31,125
- Can we trust Red?
- Red's a straight-up guy.

648
00:58:32,429 --> 00:58:35,489
There's only one reason Red
wouldn't call back.

649
00:58:35,565 --> 00:58:36,793
What's that?

650
00:58:37,133 --> 00:58:38,361
He's dead.

651
00:58:43,573 --> 00:58:44,562
Calvin?

652
00:58:45,875 --> 00:58:47,900
Get us on the first plane to Houston.

653
00:58:47,978 --> 00:58:51,914
Call the Wheeler brothers in Dallas.
Tell them to meet us at the airport.

654
00:58:52,849 --> 00:58:55,215
- Tell them we'll need some firearms.
- Done deal.

655
00:58:56,653 --> 00:59:00,749
I'm going to dump the body, so there's
no way he can be connected to you.

656
00:59:00,824 --> 00:59:04,260
I'm going to come back, get the car,
and leave Galveston.

657
00:59:06,363 --> 00:59:09,161
Listen, I think you ought to go somewhere, too.

658
00:59:10,100 --> 00:59:13,900
I don't know how they tracked me down,
but there might be more of them coming.

659
00:59:13,970 --> 00:59:17,963
It's going to blow tonight, harder than they say.

660
00:59:20,410 --> 00:59:22,071
Are you all right?

661
00:59:24,614 --> 00:59:26,844
I'll be back as soon as I can.

662
00:59:38,561 --> 00:59:39,721
May I help you?

663
00:59:39,796 --> 00:59:42,697
Dell, party of four. We're going to Houston.

664
00:59:45,235 --> 00:59:47,726
Do you have a picture ID, Mr. Dell?

665
00:59:48,705 --> 00:59:51,139
- Do you have a picture ID?
- Of who?

666
00:59:52,275 --> 00:59:54,243
Who fuckin' cares?

667
01:01:39,716 --> 01:01:41,513
Are you the grandson?

668
01:01:43,286 --> 01:01:44,548
Yes, sir.

669
01:01:45,555 --> 01:01:46,886
How is he?

670
01:01:46,990 --> 01:01:49,788
How did he get those bruises on his face?

671
01:01:50,827 --> 01:01:54,524
He fell. I should've been there.

672
01:01:55,665 --> 01:01:57,428
These things happen.

673
01:01:58,101 --> 01:02:01,264
- Can I see him?
- He's had a heart attack.

674
01:02:02,372 --> 01:02:05,808
- Is he going to make it?
- We'll have to wait and see.

675
01:02:09,579 --> 01:02:11,240
I don't know, man.

676
01:02:12,015 --> 01:02:16,247
Listen to me. I woke up this morning
and he was gone. He didn't leave a note.

677
01:02:16,453 --> 01:02:18,045
Is his stuff still there?

678
01:02:21,157 --> 01:02:23,284
Then I'm sure he'll be back.

679
01:02:25,028 --> 01:02:28,828
Listen, you don't got to worry about Jesse.
He's fine.

680
01:02:31,901 --> 01:02:34,199
Louis, Jimmy, let's go.

681
01:02:55,992 --> 01:02:57,391
Thanks, man.

682
01:03:00,763 --> 01:03:02,128
I love these things.

683
01:03:02,699 --> 01:03:04,098
Good for me.

684
01:04:01,658 --> 01:04:03,853
How come you ain't gone, son?

685
01:04:09,799 --> 01:04:11,824
I'll be here when you get back.

686
01:04:14,537 --> 01:04:15,765
Now, get.

687
01:04:38,361 --> 01:04:40,386
Jeremy, honey, come inside.

688
01:04:45,802 --> 01:04:47,770
Come on. Let's get ready for dinner.

689
01:04:49,839 --> 01:04:52,273
I'm sure he'll be back by tonight.

690
01:04:53,676 --> 01:04:55,769
I'm worried about Michelle.

691
01:04:58,414 --> 01:05:01,781
You know how it is, I really love her.

692
01:05:02,552 --> 01:05:04,213
Too much, probably.

693
01:05:06,556 --> 01:05:09,548
I think of her as delicate and easily-injured...

694
01:05:09,626 --> 01:05:12,288
...but she's about as sturdy as they come.

695
01:05:17,500 --> 01:05:20,663
The thing is, Morgan,
you never can tell with these storms.

696
01:05:20,770 --> 01:05:24,001
I was even thinking
about getting her out of the water.

697
01:05:24,641 --> 01:05:26,666
I might go to the marina after supper.

698
01:05:26,743 --> 01:05:29,541
If you're not busy, you want to come along?

699
01:05:30,980 --> 01:05:32,743
My wife just bit me.

700
01:05:33,783 --> 01:05:35,114
I have no idea.

701
01:05:43,926 --> 01:05:45,188
Nobody's home.

702
01:05:46,329 --> 01:05:49,264
Calvin, you and the boys go and check it out.

703
01:06:19,529 --> 01:06:22,089
Damn weather. How you doing?

704
01:06:22,432 --> 01:06:24,263
We're fine. How are you, ma'am?

705
01:06:24,801 --> 01:06:27,292
- Nobody home?
- Doesn't look like it.

706
01:06:28,104 --> 01:06:31,005
That's strange. Mr. Parish is always here.

707
01:06:32,108 --> 01:06:34,440
I wonder where he could've gone.

708
01:06:35,611 --> 01:06:39,308
I came to give him some cinnamon rolls.
He loves my cinnamon rolls.

709
01:06:39,782 --> 01:06:42,478
I'm Mrs. Lawson. I live down the road.

710
01:06:44,420 --> 01:06:46,547
Y'all friends of Mr. Parish?

711
01:06:47,957 --> 01:06:51,154
Ma'am! Can I see you over here
for just a minute?

712
01:06:52,595 --> 01:06:56,725
We're friends of Mr. Parish's grandson, Jesse.

713
01:06:57,433 --> 01:06:58,923
You know Jesse!

714
01:06:59,001 --> 01:07:01,697
Yes, ma'am. We go way back.
He's a good old boy.

715
01:07:01,938 --> 01:07:03,735
He sure is, ain't he?

716
01:07:04,140 --> 01:07:07,405
It's real important that we get
a hold of him. It's about a job.

717
01:07:07,477 --> 01:07:11,004
He ain't staying with his grandpapa.
He's staying with his friend Morgan.

718
01:07:14,717 --> 01:07:16,446
Hold it one minute.

719
01:07:18,154 --> 01:07:20,418
Let me see if I understand you correctly.

720
01:07:20,690 --> 01:07:23,215
You mentioned something about a job?

721
01:07:25,561 --> 01:07:28,826
You're not involved in the music business,
are you?

722
01:07:30,133 --> 01:07:31,828
Yes, ma'am.

723
01:07:32,168 --> 01:07:35,831
I can't say I'm always proud of it,
but we are in the music business.

724
01:07:37,373 --> 01:07:39,000
That's wonderful!

725
01:07:41,978 --> 01:07:44,811
Can you tell us where his friend Morgan lives?

726
01:07:45,047 --> 01:07:46,844
Sure, I can tell you.

727
01:07:47,283 --> 01:07:49,308
Jesse's going to be so happy.

728
01:07:49,452 --> 01:07:51,079
I bet he will be.

729
01:07:51,988 --> 01:07:53,615
I'm starting to get worried.

730
01:07:53,689 --> 01:07:55,088
Maybe he's at his granddad's.

731
01:07:55,158 --> 01:07:57,786
He ain't. I called over there.
There ain't no answer.

732
01:07:58,127 --> 01:08:01,119
Maybe he decided
to become a drug addict again.

733
01:08:07,670 --> 01:08:09,194
Where you been?

734
01:08:13,643 --> 01:08:15,235
What's going on?

735
01:08:15,545 --> 01:08:17,012
They're here.

736
01:08:19,148 --> 01:08:20,342
What's going on?

737
01:08:20,416 --> 01:08:24,352
- Where are you going?
- As far away as I can fuckin' get.

738
01:08:24,587 --> 01:08:26,020
For everybody's sake.

739
01:08:26,522 --> 01:08:29,685
God damn! Will somebody tell me
what's happening?

740
01:08:30,326 --> 01:08:31,987
Granddad killed someone.

741
01:08:32,061 --> 01:08:34,029
Killed someone? Who?

742
01:08:34,096 --> 01:08:37,065
I don't know. Some guy. He would've killed me.

743
01:08:37,266 --> 01:08:41,259
- Why would he have killed you?
- Because out in LA, I stole some money.

744
01:08:41,771 --> 01:08:43,295
A lot of money.

745
01:08:44,674 --> 01:08:46,801
But I got the bastard's gun.

746
01:08:48,311 --> 01:08:50,575
- Why don't you go play?
- Play what, Daddy?

747
01:08:50,646 --> 01:08:52,136
I don't know. Just go play.

748
01:08:52,215 --> 01:08:54,547
The last thing I want is to drag y'all into this.

749
01:08:54,617 --> 01:08:57,245
I'm just going to go as far away as I can.

750
01:08:57,320 --> 01:09:01,654
Call and let them know where the money is.
They'll be on my ass forever if I don't.

751
01:09:01,724 --> 01:09:05,990
